<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-975-880  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 975 880.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Dec 18 1989 v11 n51 p26(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Embedded hard disk controllers reduce hassles, options.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dryden, Patrick.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Because hard disk storage is required for most applicationsrunning on non-networked microcomputers, system and disk drivevendors have streamlined disk support by using embedded disk drivecontrollers.andP;  Drives with built-in controllers connect to the hostmotherboard, freeing a slot and delivering other benefits.andO;Integration advantages may cramp user's expansion plans, however.andO;Drives and controllers used to be developed by manufacturers butbecame separate components with the proliferation ofmicrocomputers.andP;  Compaq and Western Digital redefined the businterface signals halfway through the microcomputer decade.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Disk DrivesControllersMemory ManagementExpansionBoards-Cards.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>